dismissalText.long: c Babar Azam b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Babar Azam b Yasir Shah 38 (54b 5x4 0x6 73m) SR: 70.37

dismissalComment.html: is that a top edge? Yep. Looks for the big hit against the turn and is beaten in the flight. Mathews can't quite get as close to the ball as he wanted to with the slog sweep. That means the ball is able to spin just enough that he has to drag it away from outside off into the leg side. Azam at long-on is safe as houses

headshotImage.caption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalComment.html: Hafeez gets another left-hand batsman. Kusal left contemplating another start not converted. Pushed through outside off, non-turning ball. Kusal looks to push, or perhaps punch it through the covers. All he manages a thick edge to first slip. Sharp take from Rizwan just below chest height. Kusal did not move his feet and pays the price

too good. He is just too good against the left-handers. Angles the good length ball in to force a shot. Tharanga flails at it after lunging outside his crease. The turn is too much, the outside edge is comprehensively beaten. Sarfraz takes care of the rest. Beaten in flight.

plays back to one that he should have been forward to. That's a timely strike for Pakistan and it's from their best bowler on show so far. Beautiful control from Hafeez. Doesn't quite loop this one up, which was why Dilshan jumps back in his crease to cut. Suddenly realises the shot is nowhere near on. Tries to protect his off stump. Fails

ends his spell with a wicket. And that's his best figures in ODIs. Might need to get a gift for Rizwan for this. Beautiful low catch by him at first slip. Especially seeing as the batsman was backing away for a cut. So even if it was an edge, it would have come to him quite quickly. Nice, tight bowling from Hafeez. Good length on middle from around the wicket. Thisara was looking to slice it to third man and get off strike. But the ball went a bit too fine

headshotImage.caption: Milinda Siriwardana player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Milinda Siriwardana player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Rizwan, you little beauty! He is so good to watch in the field. Kisses the ball before tossing it away. Another skier, but this time the fielder has less distance to cover. I think he was in the covers, raced in and called for it. Anyway the only other man who could have caught it was Rahat, who you don't want under a tough catch. Rizwan has his eyes all the way on it, dives and holds on this time

dismissalComment.html: he's been sucked into the drive and the edge is safely taken. Anwar claps in glee and then morphs into an airplane. Hands spread out, mouth wide open in a yell. Good ball, better celebrations. Good length ball skirting outside off, Thirimanne is tempted into a loose shot. Looked so good only for a soft dismissal. Pakistan are ringing in the changes, and they're working

dismissalComment.html: he's fished outside off and has been caught! Sri Lanka created the pressure. They stopped the singles. They got a few balls to bounce alarmingly. Shehzad weathered through all of them and will be filthy with himself at being sucked into playing so far away from his body. Didn't move across, flashed at it and feathers a simple edge to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali c †Chandimal b Mathews 21 (29b 3x4 0x6 40m) SR: 72.41

dismissalComment.html: done him in! Chandimal and Mathews combine to bring Sri Lanka back again. It was wide, it was tempting Azhar to go for the booming drive through cover. In all honesty, the shot was on. But on a pitch where the bounce isn't true, there's always a risk involved with driving on the up. Azhar gets an under edge and Chandimal takes an absolute stunner. Stayed low, moved to his right along with the ball and snapped it up

dismissalComment.html: caught in front! Azam was walking off, but he is called back by his partner. Has a little chat with Hafeez and then makes the decision himself that he doesn't want to review. Azam goes for the sweep, but hasn't put that front leg too far across. Misses the ball hitting across the line and is struck in line with off stump, I think

headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: smashed away! That's the win. That's his fifty. That's a 1-0 lead in this five-match series. Tucks his bat under his arm as soon as he made contact after dancing down the track. So another pristine chase from Pakistan. Did you expect anything less after Pallekele?

commentPostTextItems.html: That's all we have for you. Join us again for the second ODI, which will be a day-night affair from Pallekele on July 15. Until then, its goodbye

"Great team performance, everyone played their part. Hafeez had an exceptional day. Played like a champion with ball an dbat," Azhar Ali says "Restricting Sri Lanka to 250 was great. Last 10 overs was great. Hafeez got crucial wickets at crucial times. All the bowlers were disciplined and I think it was backed up by the batsman very well. Everyone was positive and performed their roles. Nowadays you have to piclk up wickets to stop runs. That message is clear. Whenever the bowlers feel they can pick wickets, they should. Yasir is very confident. Hit for a few boundaries early on, but he's got great temeperament. Sri Lanka can come back strong and we need to be mindful of that. Really important with the team is in a rebuilding phase you need experience to guide the youngsters"

Mohammad Hafeez is the Man of the Match. "Definitely. I have to put that [scrutiny on his bowling action] aside and concentrate on what is in my hands. We wanted to have a good series in the ODIs. Wanted to continue the tempo from the Test team. It's a great game, always great to see Pakistan's young players do well [Shan Masood] played a very good innings to contribute to victory. We wanted to have a good start to the series. First the bowlers did a great job to restrict them to 250 and then we could attack. No pressure. Just played normally. It was a new plan, the green signal was given by the management. They gave me the licence to play aggressively and it worked"

"Initially 255 was below par on the wicket. It was a bit spungy and turning quite a bit as well. It got better in the second half, but we just couldn't put a score," Mathews says, "Couldn't pick up wickets at crucial stages. Hafeez batted really well. We didn't play our best cricket, but hopefully we can come back better in the next few games. Good couple of days off now, been playing non-stop. Just need to prepare mentally. No complication about the change of rules. Had a good team meeting. Keep an eye on the rules, keeps changing, makes it even harder. But we have to deal with it"

5.30 pm It was supposed to be a good total. The pitch was offering sharpish bounce to the seamers, so driving on the up was rather hard. It needed a big effort and it came from Mohammad Hafeez. A very composed century - his fourth against Sri Lanka - to blunt their attack and give them no hope of mounting a come back. Also remember that he took four good wickets earlier as well. A shoo in for the Man of the Match.

There were a few questions raised against Angelo Mathews' captaincy though. He underbowled himself and Suranga Lakmal as well. Overbowled Seekuge Prasanna who lacked for accuracy all through his spell. Lasith Malinga appeared to be struggling for fitness as well. The bowling attack lost them the game

Adnan Maqsood: "Suddenly this Pakistani side is a different team. They are denouncing all the odds - rather regularities for them - and turning it on. Something has revolutionized these boys, may be an emotional speech or a threat." --- Why a threat?

alan: "Debut for Siriwardana, but he only bowled 2 overs. SL have too many so called allrounders that we don't know whether they will bat or bowl in any particular day. Only god knows what they will do on a day. "

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Rizwan b Rahat Ali
dismissalText.commentary: Milinda Siriwardana c Mohammad Rizwan b Rahat Ali 22 (21b 2x4 1x6 21m) SR: 104.76

dismissalComment.html: Rizwan, you little beauty! He is so good to watch in the field. Kisses the ball before tossing it away. Another skier, but this time the fielder has less distance to cover. I think he was in the covers, raced in and called for it. Anyway the only other man who could have caught it was Rahat, who you don't want under a tough catch. Rizwan has his eyes all the way on it, dives and holds on this time

headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali c †Chandimal b Mathews 21 (29b 3x4 0x6 40m) SR: 72.41

dismissalComment.html: done him in! Chandimal and Mathews combine to bring Sri Lanka back again. It was wide, it was tempting Azhar to go for the booming drive through cover. In all honesty, the shot was on. But on a pitch where the bounce isn't true, there's always a risk involved with driving on the up. Azhar gets an under edge and Chandimal takes an absolute stunner. Stayed low, moved to his right along with the ball and snapped it up

headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c †Chandimal b Lakmal 29 (39b 4x4 0x6 61m) SR: 74.35

dismissalComment.html: he's fished outside off and has been caught! Sri Lanka created the pressure. They stopped the singles. They got a few balls to bounce alarmingly. Shehzad weathered through all of them and will be filthy with himself at being sucked into playing so far away from his body. Didn't move across, flashed at it and feathers a simple edge to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c & b NLTC Perera 103 (95b 10x4 4x6 115m) SR: 108.42

dismissalComment.html: pops up a return catch! Jumps down the track for no good reason, Thisara bowls it short and quick on middle. Cramps the batsman up. Goes for a panicked pull, gets it on the splice and gives a simple catch to Thisara. But he's done his work. Gets a hug from his captain, a pat on the back from his coach. Good innings

dismissalText.commentary: Babar Azam lbw b Dilshan 25 (30b 3x4 0x6 48m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: caught in front! Azam was walking off, but he is called back by his partner. Has a little chat with Hafeez and then makes the decision himself that he doesn't want to review. Azam goes for the sweep, but hasn't put that front leg too far across. Misses the ball hitting across the line and is struck in line with off stump, I think
